<subsection xml:id="subsec-congruent-and-similar-shapes-in-coordinate-plane">
    <title>Congruent and Similar Shapes in Coordinate Plane</title>
    <p>
        <term>Congruent Shapes:</term> Two shapes are congruent if they have the same size and shape but may be rotated, reflected, or translated. Their corresponding sides and angles are equal.
    </p>
    <p>
        <term>Similar Shapes:</term> Two shapes are similar if they have the same shape but different sizes. Their corresponding angles are equal, and their sides are proportional.
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
          <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p>
          Trace and cut out the following shapes on a graph paper.
        </p>
  
        <image>
          <shortdescription></shortdescription>
          <latex-image label="shapes_1">
            \begin{tikzpicture}
               % Draw the grid lines
              \draw[step=1,gray,very thin] (-9,-6) grid (9,6);
                
              \fill[purple,opacity=0.3](-7,5) -- (-7,3) -- (-5,3) -- cycle;
              \draw[purple,thick] (-7,5) -- (-7,3) -- (-5,3) -- cycle;
              \node[purple] at (-6,3.5) {$A$};
  
              \fill[blue,opacity=0.3](-4,5) -- (-2,5) -- (-2,3) -- (-4,3) -- cycle;
              \draw[blue,thick] (-4,5) -- (-2,5) -- (-2,3) -- (-4,3) -- cycle;
              \node[blue] at (-3,4) {$B$};
  
              \fill[blue,opacity=0.3](-1,5) -- (2,5) -- (2,3) -- (-1,3) -- cycle;
              \draw[blue,thick] (-1,5) -- (2,5) -- (2,3) -- (-1,3)-- cycle;
              \node[blue] at (-.5,4) {$C$};
  
              \fill[red,opacity=0.3](3,5) -- (6,5) -- (3,3) -- cycle;
              \draw[red,thick] (3,5) -- (6,5) -- (3,3) -- cycle;
              \node[red] at (3.5,4.5) {$D$};
  
              \fill[orange,opacity=0.3](-7,2) -- (-5,2) -- (-4,0) -- (-8,0) -- cycle;
              \draw[orange,thick] (-7,2) -- (-5,2) -- (-4,0) -- (-8,0) -- cycle;
